-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-04/harvard-falls-to-60-54-defeat-to-unranked-fordham-in-college-basketball.html
Bryan Smith scored 22 points to lead
 Fordham University  to a 60-54 win over 21st-ranked  Harvard
University  in college basketball.  Itâ€™s the first victory for Fordham (7-6) over a ranked team
since Feb. 26, 1978, when the Rams beat No. 18 Georgetown 63-59.  Chris Gaston added 18 points and 10 rebounds as the Rams
hit 49 percent of their shots from the floor and 71 percent from
the free-throw line at Rose Hill Gym in  New York .  Brandyn Curry scored 15 points for the Crimson, who
connected on 36 percent of their shots from the floor and 50
percent from the free-throw line. Harvard (12-2) held a 27-24
halftime lead.  The game was the 11th between the Rams and the Crimson.
Fordham leads the series, which started in 1962, 8-3 and has won
all four meetings against Harvard at Rose Hill Gym.  To contact the reporter on this story:
